  <abstract>Tom Ludwig's diary of his activities in Kodak, Tennessee. He gives his opinion on the development of local union leaders and participation in the meeting. He lists women participating as a benchmark for measuring success of these meetings, noting "now they get up and speak their piece about the tobacco allotment or anything else." He also mentions the potential for a song festival "using Zilphia's techniques."</abstract>
